Hello,

Can you please confirm if you have any allowlists setup?
Also please collect a set of logs following the steps below.

To gather the needed logs, please go to Device Control -> Computers or Users and filter for the PC name or User name, and hit Apply
[cid:image003.png@01DBA57F.1EED0100]
In the Action menu of the computer/user, select Manage settings
[cid:image004.png@01DBA57F.1EED0100]
In the Debug Mode section please select Debug from the dropdown and Save
[cid:image005.png@01DBA57F.1EED0100]
After this please update the policies on the Computer and reproduce the issue a couple of times.
Return to the Console and go to Device Control -> Computers or users and repeat the same filter as before
In the Actions menu please select Collect Diagnostics and after 10 minutes In the same menu choose Go to Diagnostics Data
[cid:image006.png@01DBA57F.1EED0100]
In the table press on the download icon from the Actions column and send the archive as an attachment
[cid:image007.png@01DBA57F.1EED0100]Once the archive is sent, please return to the computer/user settings and disable the debug mode in one of the two ways depending on what the case is.
If you want to return the computer to the Global settings, then press the Restore Global/Default Settings button at the bottom of the page.
If you have custom rules or settings for the computer, after disabling the debug mode, just hit Save.

Kind regards
__________________
Andrei Pop | Technical Support Engineer
Netwrix Endpoint Protector
[https://www.endpointprotector.com/images/img/email_resources/email_signature_epp_logo_small.png]

Hello,

Can you please confirm if you have any allowlists setup?
Also please collect a set of logs following the steps below.

To gather the needed logs, please go to Device Control -> Computers or Users and filter for the PC name or User name, and hit Apply

In the Action menu of the computer/user, select Manage settings

In the Debug Mode section please select Debug from the dropdown and Save

After this please update the policies on the Computer and reproduce the issue a couple of times.
Return to the Console and go to Device Control -> Computers or users and repeat the same filter as before
In the Actions menu please select Collect Diagnostics and after 10 minutes In the same menu choose Go to Diagnostics Data

In the table press on the download icon from the Actions column and send the archive as an attachment
Once the archive is sent, please return to the computer/user settings and disable the debug mode in one of the two ways depending on what the case is.
If you want to return the computer to the Global settings, then press the Restore Global/Default Settings button at the bottom of the page.
If you have custom rules or settings for the computer, after disabling the debug mode, just hit Save.

Kind regards

Hello,

Can you please confirm if you have any allowlists setup?
Also please collect a set of logs following the steps below.

To gather the needed logs, please go to Device Control -> Computers or Users and filter for the PC name or User name, and hit Apply

In the Action menu of the computer/user, select Manage settings

In the Debug Mode section please select Debug from the dropdown and Save

After this please update the policies on the Computer and reproduce the issue a couple of times.
Return to the Console and go to Device Control -> Computers or users and repeat the same filter as before
In the Actions menu please select Collect Diagnostics and after 10 minutes In the same menu choose Go to Diagnostics Data

In the table press on the download icon from the Actions column and send the archive as an attachment
Once the archive is sent, please return to the computer/user settings and disable the debug mode in one of the two ways depending on what the case is.
If you want to return the computer to the Global settings, then press the Restore Global/Default Settings button at the bottom of the page.
If you have custom rules or settings for the computer, after disabling the debug mode, just hit Save.

Kind regards
__________________
Andrei Pop | Technical Support Engineer

Hello,

Can you please confirm if you have any allowlists setup?
Also please collect a set of logs following the steps below.

To gather the needed logs, please go to Device Control -> Computers or Users and filter for the PC name or User name, and hit Apply
[cid:image003.png@01DBA582.F0507DA0]
In the Action menu of the computer/user, select Manage settings
[cid:image004.png@01DBA582.F0507DA0]
In the Debug Mode section please select Debug from the dropdown and Save
[cid:image005.png@01DBA582.F0507DA0]
After this please update the policies on the Computer and reproduce the issue a couple of times.
Return to the Console and go to Device Control -> Computers or users and repeat the same filter as before
In the Actions menu please select Collect Diagnostics and after 10 minutes In the same menu choose Go to Diagnostics Data
[cid:image006.png@01DBA582.F0507DA0]
In the table press on the download icon from the Actions column and send the archive as an attachment
[cid:image007.png@01DBA582.F0507DA0]Once the archive is sent, please return to the computer/user settings and disable the debug mode in one of the two ways depending on what the case is.
If you want to return the computer to the Global settings, then press the Restore Global/Default Settings button at the bottom of the page.
If you have custom rules or settings for the computer, after disabling the debug mode, just hit Save.

Kind regards

sophospsmartbannerend

Hello,

Can you please confirm if you have any allowlists setup?
Also please collect a set of logs following the steps below.

To gather the needed logs, please go to Device Control -> Computers or Users and filter for the PC name or User name, and hit Apply
[cid:image003.png@01DBA588.E420ED20]
In the Action menu of the computer/user, select Manage settings
[cid:image004.png@01DBA588.E420ED20]
In the Debug Mode section please select Debug from the dropdown and Save
[cid:image005.png@01DBA588.E420ED20]
After this please update the policies on the Computer and reproduce the issue a couple of times.
Return to the Console and go to Device Control -> Computers or users and repeat the same filter as before
In the Actions menu please select Collect Diagnostics and after 10 minutes In the same menu choose Go to Diagnostics Data
[cid:image006.png@01DBA588.E420ED20]
In the table press on the download icon from the Actions column and send the archive as an attachment
[cid:image007.png@01DBA588.E420ED20]Once the archive is sent, please return to the computer/user settings and disable the debug mode in one of the two ways depending on what the case is.
If you want to return the computer to the Global settings, then press the Restore Global/Default Settings button at the bottom of the page.
If you have custom rules or settings for the computer, after disabling the debug mode, just hit Save.

Kind regards

Hello,

Can you please confirm if you have any allowlists setup?
Also please collect a set of logs following the steps below.

To gather the needed logs, please go to Device Control -> Computers or Users and filter for the PC name or User name, and hit Apply

In the Action menu of the computer/user, select Manage settings

In the Debug Mode section please select Debug from the dropdown and Save

After this please update the policies on the Computer and reproduce the issue a couple of times.
Return to the Console and go to Device Control -> Computers or users and repeat the same filter as before
In the Actions menu please select Collect Diagnostics and after 10 minutes In the same menu choose Go to Diagnostics Data

In the table press on the download icon from the Actions column and send the archive as an attachment
Once the archive is sent, please return to the computer/user settings and disable the debug mode in one of the two ways depending on what the case is.
If you want to return the computer to the Global settings, then press the Restore Global/Default Settings button at the bottom of the page.
If you have custom rules or settings for the computer, after disabling the debug mode, just hit Save.

Kind regards
__________________
Andrei Pop | Technical Support Engineer

Hello,

Can you please confirm if you have any allowlists setup?
Also please collect a set of logs following the steps below.

To gather the needed logs, please go to Device Control -> Computers or Users and filter for the PC name or User name, and hit Apply
[cid:556d36bc-9f60-4e83-a1d1-957e9b567a55@Image_12_]
In the Action menu of the computer/user, select Manage settings
[cid:cbdb20aa-7591-44c8-b88f-c4432507a3ff@Image_13_]
In the Debug Mode section please select Debug from the dropdown and Save
[cid:090f5bfc-da28-4bde-9f4a-62022402722e@Image_14_]
After this please update the policies on the Computer and reproduce the issue a couple of times.
Return to the Console and go to Device Control -> Computers or users and repeat the same filter as before
In the Actions menu please select Collect Diagnostics and after 10 minutes In the same menu choose Go to Diagnostics Data
[cid:3d7f4a90-25dc-4a4a-9d58-7bd20c15c6c2@Image_15_]
In the table press on the download icon from the Actions column and send the archive as an attachment
[cid:7a5fef51-eb9b-4838-a0f6-f051bdf4a775@Image_16_]Once the archive is sent, please return to the computer/user settings and disable the debug mode in one of the two ways depending on what the case is.
If you want to return the computer to the Global settings, then press the Restore Global/Default Settings button at the bottom of the page.
If you have custom rules or settings for the computer, after disabling the debug mode, just hit Save.

Kind regards

Hello,

Can you please confirm if you have any allowlists setup?
Also please collect a set of logs following the steps below.

To gather the needed logs, please go to Device Control -> Computers or Users and filter for the PC name or User name, and hit Apply

In the Action menu of the computer/user, select Manage settings

In the Debug Mode section please select Debug from the dropdown and Save

After this please update the policies on the Computer and reproduce the issue a couple of times.
Return to the Console and go to Device Control -> Computers or users and repeat the same filter as before
In the Actions menu please select Collect Diagnostics and after 10 minutes In the same menu choose Go to Diagnostics Data

In the table press on the download icon from the Actions column and send the archive as an attachment
Once the archive is sent, please return to the computer/user settings and disable the debug mode in one of the two ways depending on what the case is.
If you want to return the computer to the Global settings, then press the Restore Global/Default Settings button at the bottom of the page.
If you have custom rules or settings for the computer, after disabling the debug mode, just hit Save.

Kind regards
__________________

Hello,

Can you please confirm if you have any allowlists setup?
Also please collect a set of logs following the steps below.

To gather the needed logs, please go to Device Control -> Computers or Users and filter for the PC name or User name, and hit Apply
[cid:c3f071f1-ff8c-4ea1-bea0-a09823d11dfa@Image_14_]
In the Action menu of the computer/user, select Manage settings
[cid:751e9cd4-6029-437f-bb5f-ae98d01cc3a3@Image_15_]
In the Debug Mode section please select Debug from the dropdown and Save
[cid:13ccb094-2558-45a9-bdbf-20f7fa12dd02@Image_16_]
After this please update the policies on the Computer and reproduce the issue a couple of times.
Return to the Console and go to Device Control -> Computers or users and repeat the same filter as before
In the Actions menu please select Collect Diagnostics and after 10 minutes In the same menu choose Go to Diagnostics Data
[cid:5cfc21a6-5e82-482d-9bd6-5b3b4196ae28@Image_17_]
In the table press on the download icon from the Actions column and send the archive as an attachment
[cid:d68b0a88-684f-4d37-94d9-10016ac1ee70@Image_18_]Once the archive is sent, please return to the computer/user settings and disable the debug mode in one of the two ways depending on what the case is.
If you want to return the computer to the Global settings, then press the Restore Global/Default Settings button at the bottom of the page.
If you have custom rules or settings for the computer, after disabling the debug mode, just hit Save.

Kind regards

In the Action menu of the computer/user, select Manage settings

In the Debug Mode section please select Debug from the dropdown and Save

After this please update the policies on the Computer and reproduce the issue a couple of times.
Return to the Console and go to Device Control -> Computers or users and repeat the same filter as before
In the Actions menu please select Collect Diagnostics and after 10 minutes In the same menu choose Go to Diagnostics Data

In the table press on the download icon from the Actions column and send the archive as an attachment
Once the archive is sent, please return to the computer/user settings and disable the debug mode in one of the two ways depending on what the case is.
If you want to return the computer to the Global settings, then press the Restore Global/Default Settings button at the bottom of the page.
If you have custom rules or settings for the computer, after disabling the debug mode, just hit Save.

Kind regards

Hello,

Can you please confirm if you have any allowlists setup?
Also please collect a set of logs following the steps below.

To gather the needed logs, please go to Device Control -> Computers or Users and filter for the PC name or User name, and hit Apply
[cid:73cee7e7-e84d-427f-8ce2-51214b241c13@Image_16_]
In the Action menu of the computer/user, select Manage settings
[cid:23039969-df71-4f9d-bebb-d99534380f62@Image_17_]
In the Debug Mode section please select Debug from the dropdown and Save
[cid:eca8184c-79a1-40b1-a34e-65d199db80c1@Image_18_]
After this please update the policies on the Computer and reproduce the issue a couple of times.
Return to the Console and go to Device Control -> Computers or users and repeat the same filter as before
In the Actions menu please select Collect Diagnostics and after 10 minutes In the same menu choose Go to Diagnostics Data
[cid:65a62f9a-be7e-4663-a7a8-e0df22c315be@Image_19_]
In the table press on the download icon from the Actions column and send the archive as an attachment
[cid:1a43a741-f046-40a2-8225-7ddb81ed2cd2@Image_20_]Once the archive is sent, please return to the computer/user settings and disable the debug mode in one of the two ways depending on what the case is.
If you want to return the computer to the Global settings, then press the Restore Global/Default Settings button at the bottom of the page.
If you have custom rules or settings for the computer, after disabling the debug mode, just hit Save.

Kind regards

Hello,

Can you please confirm if you have any allowlists setup?
Also please collect a set of logs following the steps below.

To gather the needed logs, please go to Device Control -> Computers or Users and filter for the PC name or User name, and hit Apply

In the Action menu of the computer/user, select Manage settings

In the Debug Mode section please select Debug from the dropdown and Save

After this please update the policies on the Computer and reproduce the issue a couple of times.
Return to the Console and go to Device Control -> Computers or users and repeat the same filter as before
In the Actions menu please select Collect Diagnostics and after 10 minutes In the same menu choose Go to Diagnostics Data

In the table press on the download icon from the Actions column and send the archive as an attachment
Once the archive is sent, please return to the computer/user settings and disable the debug mode in one of the two ways depending on what the case is.
If you want to return the computer to the Global settings, then press the Restore Global/Default Settings button at the bottom of the page.
If you have custom rules or settings for the computer, after disabling the debug mode, just hit Save.

Kind regards

Hello,

Can you please confirm if you have any allowlists setup?
Also please collect a set of logs following the steps below.

To gather the needed logs, please go to Device Control -> Computers or Users and filter for the PC name or User name, and hit Apply
[cid:e0a23564-4949-40a6-ac59-f59753115894@Image_18_]
In the Action menu of the computer/user, select Manage settings
[cid:ccdddc39-53d9-4e42-927c-2d3c985974c8@Image_19_]
In the Debug Mode section please select Debug from the dropdown and Save
[cid:9b710842-5df3-4e1d-84ad-c14edfc6edd3@Image_20_]
After this please update the policies on the Computer and reproduce the issue a couple of times.
Return to the Console and go to Device Control -> Computers or users and repeat the same filter as before
In the Actions menu please select Collect Diagnostics and after 10 minutes In the same menu choose Go to Diagnostics Data
[cid:aa956313-5885-4b68-b5b2-2069cc2cd11c@Image_21_]
In the table press on the download icon from the Actions column and send the archive as an attachment
[cid:4bd1c7bc-8b7f-4b0c-9fad-519e42c48699@Image_22_]Once the archive is sent, please return to the computer/user settings and disable the debug mode in one of the two ways depending on what the case is.
If you want to return the computer to the Global settings, then press the Restore Global/Default Settings button at the bottom of the page.
If you have custom rules or settings for the computer, after disabling the debug mode, just hit Save.

Kind regards
